race.comment: ELECTRIC STAR (9) resumes having been tipped out off a narrow maiden win here on debut, backed into an even money favourite and getting the job done. Very wary of how much improvement he'll make for the sharp stable. Looks well placed to remain unbeaten on resumption. JAHANGIR (3) resumes for his second campaign. He won 2/4 starts in his maiden campaign and did some nice things. He can land in a good spot from the soft gate and measure right up. IMMINANCE (11) is a chance on best form having won well two back. FULLY CALCULATED (6) felt the pinch late first-up at Morphettville when having to do a bit or work early. Fitter for that effort and he's likely to have come on from that effort.
